You've used the windowLightStatusBar property to change the the color of the text and icons in the status bar based on the day or night theme. But if you have "Auto day-night mode" activated and the theme changes from day to night as you're viewing the app, the color of the status bar text and icons remains the same (making them illegible).

The solution I've implemented in my app to solve this problem is shown below. Just call this method from onResume() in each Activity:

    public static void setStatusBarAndNavigationBarColors(Activity activity) {
        if (Build.VERSION.SDK_INT > Build.VERSION_CODES.O) {
            View view = activity.getWindow().getDecorView();
            int flagset = view.getSystemUiVisibility();
            boolean containsLightStatusBarFlag = (flagset|View.SYSTEM_UI_FLAG_LIGHT_STATUS_BAR) == flagset;
            int currentNightMode = activity.getResources().getConfiguration().uiMode & Configuration.UI_MODE_NIGHT_MASK;
            if (currentNightMode == Configuration.UI_MODE_NIGHT_YES) {
                if (containsLightStatusBarFlag) {
                    flagset = flagset&(~View.SYSTEM_UI_FLAG_LIGHT_STATUS_BAR);
                    flagset = flagset&(~View.SYSTEM_UI_FLAG_LIGHT_NAVIGATION_BAR);
                }
            }
            else {
                if (!containsLightStatusBarFlag) {
                    flagset = flagset|View.SYSTEM_UI_FLAG_LIGHT_STATUS_BAR;
                    flagset = flagset|View.SYSTEM_UI_FLAG_LIGHT_NAVIGATION_BAR;
                }
            }

            view.setSystemUiVisibility(flagset);
            activity.getWindow().setStatusBarColor(ContextCompat.getColor(activity, R.color.colorStatusBar));
            activity.getWindow().setNavigationBarColor(ContextCompat.getColor(activity, R.color.colorBackground));
        }
    }

Reproduce:

1. Launch app
2. In `List display options`, set `Swipe left to` to `None` (default should be `Save`)
3. Return to list
4. Use your **RIGHT** hand to open the context menu for an item and then click `Save`.
5. Use your **LEFT** hand to swipe from left on an item.
6. Step 5 should be finished very quickly after the clicking of `Save`

